
--- Captcha Bypass Brute Force ---

Captcha is a security mechanism used in web applications to distinguish between humans and bots. However, when captchas are improperly implemented or weakly designed, they can be bypassed with brute-force attacks.

Brute-force attacks aimed at bypassing captcha protection can be carried out using several different methods.

1. Predictable Codes: Some captcha systems rely on certain algorithms, making the codes predictable. For example, they may operate within a specific range of numbers or follow a pattern. In this case, attackers can brute-force predictable codes.
2. Repeated Codes: If captcha codes in a system are repeatedly reused, attackers can identify these codes through brute-force attacks.
3. Machine Learning Recognition: More advanced attacks may use machine learning or OCR (optical character recognition) technology to recognize captcha images.

